description: Fix compatibility with Electron 12. This is only breaking if you are currently only creating a store (with `new Store();`) in the renderer process, and not in the Main process. In this case you will have to call `Store.initRenderer()` in the Main process (See: [Store.initRenderer()](https://github.com/MehediH/electron-store/blob/master/readme.md#initrenderer)). The renderer process is defined in a separate js file (usually `renderer.js`). For more information on the entire Process Model including the renderer process see: https://www.electronjs.org/docs/latest/tutorial/process-model.
Require Electron 11. electron-store@7.0.0 requires you to have installed Electron ^11, where it previously was Electron 9
Make the clearInvalidConfig option false by default
